This paper is about natural language understanding and dialogue systems, which are typically studied in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also involves machine learning techniques and algorithms, which are commonly studied in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the evaluation of the proposed approach, which falls under the category of software engineering and development (cs.SD). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the proposed approach in chatbots and spoken dialogue systems, which are relevant to the field of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
